value.title: GOP growing more indifferent with Trump controversies as election nears
value.excerpt: Public health experts reacted with alarm after President Donald Trump held an indoor rally with thousands of maskless supporters at a packed arena in Nevada amid the deadly coronavirus pandemic.

value.title: Mike Pence: Florida and Arizona are “Must Win” States for November
value.excerpt: The battleground states of Florida, Arizona, Pennsylvania and Michigan indicate a tight race for the presidency, as Biden leads by less than five percent in all three states on Wednesday.

value.title: Oops: VP Mike Pence missing from some Michigan ballots
value.excerpt: Local election clerks in Michigan downloading absentee ballots for residents overseas were given ballots that listed President Donald Trump’s Republican running mate as Jeremy Cohen, not Mike Pence

value.title: Kamala Harris: Wildfires burning in Western United States 'utterly predictable'
value.excerpt: Democratic vice presidential candidate Sen. Kamala Harris described the wildfires ravaging the Western United States as "utterly predictable" as she traveled to California on Tuesday.

value.title: Late Night Fears ‘Trump Fever’ After His Indoor Rally in Nevada
value.excerpt: It looks like the next long-term residency in Las Vegas will be the coronavirus,” Jimmy Fallon said on Monday’s “Tonight Show.”

value.title: Top Trump health appointee Michael Caputo warns of armed insurrection after election
value.excerpt: The assistant secretary for public affairs at the Department of Health and Human Services promoted conspiracy theories in a Facebook Live event.

value.title: Victor Davis Hanson argues Biden is being ‘held hostage’ by his own party
value.excerpt: Hoover Institution Senior Fellow Victor Davis Hanson said Joe Biden is being held hostage by the Democrats as to not compromise his own campaign.

value.title: Trump administration blocks some Xinjiang goods from China suspected of being made with slave labor
value.excerpt: The Trump administration issued new import restrictions on Monday against Chinese companies it accuses of using slave labor, including products from suspected mass prison camps in China's western Xinjiang region.

value.title: Steil Joined Vice President Mike Pence in Janesville
value.excerpt: Congressman Bryan Steil (R-Janesville) got to meet the Vice President Mike Pence in his hometown of Janesville on Monday.

value.title: Joe Biden assembles legal team ahead of divisive 2020 election
value.excerpt: Democrat Joe Biden is assembling a team of top lawyers in anticipation of court challenges to the election process that could ultimately determine who wins the race for the White House.

value.title: Netflix star under FBI investigation for soliciting sex from minors previously held Instagram session with Biden
value.excerpt: A popular Netflix personality who is reportedly under FBI investigation for soliciting nude photos from minors helped boost Joe Biden's presidential campaign earlier this year.

value.title: Kid Rock performs at Trump rally in Michigan, announces 'one last monster tour' coming
value.excerpt: On a night that felt like a late-summer concert, Kid Rock joined Donald Trump Jr. and supporters of the president at a campaign rally east of Detroit.

value.title: Trump HHS spokesperson Michael Caputo deletes Twitter account after late-night rant
value.excerpt: The top spokesperson for the Department of Health and Human Services deleted his Twitter in the aftermath of a late-night rant in which he suggested tear gassing journalists and battled with other users on the social media platform.

value.title: New York Times: Top HHS spokesman runs through conspiracies in video and claims without evidence CDC scientists are working to resist Trump
value.excerpt: The top spokesman for the Department of Health and Human Services issued an extraordinary broadside on Sunday against career government scientists, accusing them of "sedition" in their response to coronavirus and claiming without evidence that a critical federal health agency has a "resistance unit"

value.title: Lt. Col. Vindman says he now identifies as a 'Never Trumper'
value.excerpt: Lt. Col. Alexander Vindman says he now identifies as a "Never Trumper" following his official retirement from the military.

value.title: Trump baselessly questions climate science during California wildfire briefing
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump on Monday baselessly asserted that climate change is not playing a role in the catastrophic wildfires overtaking forests across the west, rebutting an official briefing him who pleaded for the President listen to the science.

value.title: Trump awards Distinguished Flying Cross to 7 California National Guard members
value.excerpt: President Trump on Monday awarded the Distinguished Flying Cross to seven members of the California National Guard who helped rescue over 200 people earlier this month from the massive wildfire.

value.title: Roger Stone calls for Trump to declare 'martial law' if he loses the election — and order arrests of Mark Zuckerberg, Tim Cook, and the Clintons
value.excerpt: "They want to play war — this is war," Stone remarked as he stirred baseless fears of electoral fraud and urged President Donald Trump to seize power.

value.title: Michael Cohen, Trump's former attorney, calls him 'absolutely morally bankrupt'
value.excerpt: Trump's former personal attorney, Michael Cohen, said his new book will give Americans a look at the "real" Donald Trump. “I am explaining to people that this is the real Donald Trump,” Cohen, speaking from home confinement,

value.title: Fact check: Trump makes four false claims in one sentence
value.excerpt: In what may be a new record for President Donald Trump, he made four false claims in one sentence of a tweet on Saturday.

value.title: Trump says 'football is boring as hell' at Nevada rally, continuing his grievance against racial injustice protests
value.excerpt: At a weekend rally in Nevada, the president continued his attacks on NFL players who protest racial injustice and police brutality on the field.

value.title: Trump campaign returns to economy with 8-figure ad buy, calls it ‘defining issue in this race’
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign is set to release a mid-eight-figure ad buy Tuesday touting the economy during President Trump's first term after a recent emphasis on "law and order" messaging, saying the economy is the "defining issue" of the 2020 presidential race, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Joe Biden says US is facing 'one of the most difficult moments in our history'
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential nominee Joe Biden said Monday that the United States is facing one of the most difficult moments in the nation's history, with "four historic crises all at the same time."

value.title: GOP chairman to release interim report on Biden probe 'in about a week'
value.excerpt: Senate Homeland Security Chairman Ron Johnson (R-Wis.) said on Monday that he will soon release an interim report from his months-long probe involving the Obama administration and Hunter Biden.

value.title: Pence cancels a plan to attend a fund-raiser hosted by QAnon supporters.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has called off plans to attend a fund-raiser in Bozeman, Mont., on Monday evening hosted by a couple who have shown support for QAnon, the convoluted conspiracy theory built around the notion of a deep-state cabal of Satan-worshiping pedophiles and their powerful Democratic backers.
